Author: Strob#3417
Content: @NutellaLicka You mean with other coin than Pirate? Pirate does not have transparent address. With other coin you just click Receive=>Get new address=>transparent address. (v0.2.44c)

Author: NutellaLicka#4241
Content: No I mean for Pirate. In Pirate you still have the ability to have a transparent address, you're just unable to send funds to anything but a Z address (no T -> T). Pools require a Taddr as coinbase is paid out in it. You can easily use CLI to do it, I am just asking for a friend as they're using windows and require a Taddr. Since Agama has updated, they took the option out for Pirate. I was asking if there were still ways to get one in Agama.

Author: Strob#3417
Content: Ok sorry I didn't know that. Thanks for the info.

Author: Strob#3417
Content: I mine without a taddress with a pool and it works so far.

Author: Strob#3417
Content: Do you mean if I use a transparent address intead I will make more with the coinbase?

Author: NutellaLicka#4241
Content: No worries. If you're pointing hash at a public pool (i.e https://minethepiratechain.black) you are required to use a Zaddr. If you run your own pool, or wish to create one, you need a Taddr to receive the funds. The pool software then shields these amounts in order to pay out to members who point their hash at the pool.
